sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant ODHWebhook as ODH Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS (service CA)
    participant ODHCtrl as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant NotebookCtrl as Notebook Controller
    participant Gateway as Gateway (data-science-gateway)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Notebook as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant DSPA as DSPA CR / S3 Secrets

    Note over User, Notebook: Flow 1: Notebook Creation and Access (Auth-Enabled)

    User->>K8sAPI: POST Notebook CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>ODHWebhook: /mutate-notebook-v1<br/>TLS client cert
    Note right of ODHWebhook: Injects kube-rbac-proxy sidecar,<br/>resolves ImageStream images,<br/>mounts CA bundles & pipeline config,<br/>injects proxy/MLflow env vars

    ODHWebhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Notebook CR

    par ODH Controller Reconciliation
        ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute<br/>(path: /notebook/{ns}/{name})
        ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ReferenceGrant<br/>(cross-namespace backend ref)
        ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>(allow 8888 + 8443)
        ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create kube-rbac-proxy<br/>Service, ConfigMap, TLS Secret,<br/>ClusterRoleBinding
    and Notebook Controller Reconciliation
        NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet<br/>(notebook pod)
        NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ClusterIP Service<br/>(80 → 8888)
    end

    Note over User, Notebook: User Accesses Notebook

    User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>KRBP: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: TokenReview<br/>(validate user token)
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Token valid
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(check 'get' on 'notebooks')
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Access granted
    KRBP->>Notebook: Forward to notebook<br/>HTTP/8888 (localhost)
    Notebook-->>KRBP: Response
    KRBP-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>User: Notebook UI

    Note over User, Notebook: Flow 2: Notebook Idle Culling

    loop Every IDLENESS_CHECK_PERIOD (default: 1 min)
        NotebookCtrl->>Notebook: GET /api/kernels<br/>HTTP/8888 (in-cluster)
        Notebook-->>NotebookCtrl: Kernel list
        NotebookCtrl->>Notebook: GET /api/terminals<br/>HTTP/8888 (in-cluster)
        Notebook-->>NotebookCtrl: Terminal list
    end

    Note right of NotebookCtrl: If idle > CULL_IDLE_TIME (default: 1440 min)
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Patch Notebook annotation<br/>kubeflow-resource-stopped
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Scale StatefulSet to 0

    Note over User, Notebook: Flow 3: DSPA Pipeline Secret Injection

    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Read DSPA CR<br/>(named 'dspa' in notebook ns)
    K8sAPI-->>ODHCtrl: DSPA spec (S3 config)
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Read S3 credential Secret<br/>(from DSPA spec)
    K8sAPI-->>ODHCtrl: S3 credentials
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create/Update ds-pipeline-config Secret<br/>(Elyra pipeline runtime config)
